Anthrax, France
--------------------
Information received on 3 Aug 2016 from Dr Loic Evain, Directeur Général adjoint, CVO, Direction générale de l'alimentation, Ministère de l'Agriculture, de l'Agroalimentaire et de la Forêt, Paris, France

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 26 Jul 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 2 Aug 2016
Report date: 2 Aug 2016
Date submitted to OIE: 3 Aug 2016
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: Jun 2008
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, Laboratory (advanced), Necropsy
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Montgreleix, Montgreleix, Cantal
Date of start of the outbreak: 26 Jul 2016
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected: animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 181 / 4 / 4 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 2.21 / 2.21 / 100 / 2.21
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter
Affected population: 4 bovines have shown symptoms and died since 26 Jul 2016. Anthrax is historically known on these pastures. A vaccination campaign is being implemented.

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Reoccurrence

Control measures:
Measures applied: Movement control inside the country; Vaccination in response to the outbreak (s); Disinfection / Disinfestation; Traceability; No treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Maisons Alfort Animal health laboratory - Anses (National laboratory) / Cattle / bacteriological examination / 2 Aug 2016 / Positive

Future Reporting: The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above. MHJ]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[There were 2 outbreaks involving cattle in Cantal in 2003, 2 bovine outbreaks in 2006, and a single outbreak in 2008. So it is an area with a history. Otherwise France is becoming truly sporadic for this disease. - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4394822,34951.]
